article.description: — Isiah Small registered 17 points and seven rebounds as Texas State beat Louisiana-Monroe 58-49 on Friday.
article.headline: Small scores 17 to lead Texas St by Louisiana- Monroe 58-49
article.linkText: Small scores 17 to lead Texas St by Louisiana- Monroe 58-49
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- — Isiah Small registered 17 points and seven rebounds as Texas State beat Louisiana-Monroe 58-49 on Friday. Mason Harrell had 11 points for Texas State (17-6, 11-3 Sun Belt Conference), which won its sixth straight game. Alonzo Sule added 10 points. Marco Morency had 13 points for the Warhawks (7-17, 5-12). Josh Nicholas added 10 points. The Bobcats are undefeated in three games against the Warhawks this season. Most recently, Texas State defeated ULM 69-63 on Jan. 23. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
